title: Dewey runner qualifies for state meet
text:
Dewey runner qualifies for state meet By Mike Tupa mtupa@examiner-enterprise.com 
Dewey High School cross country warrior Travis Black is not only a Grade A runner. 
He’s improved to Grade A-plus by qualifying for this week’s Class 3A state meet, to be held in Shawnee. 
Black earned the opportunity by finishing 12th (19:19.25) in last week’s regional meet 5K, hosted by Chisholm. 
He may have company on the course at Shawnee if Lady Dogger pacer Mia Knight makes the at-large cut for the girls. 
Knight came in 28th in the regional girls run and had to wait until today to find out whether she made the field. 
Overall, the Dewey cross country team enjoyed a solid day in Chisholm. 
The Doggers barely missed out qualifying as an entire team for state. Only the first five teams earned that distinction. Dewey came in sixth. 
Rounding out Dewey’s regional boys participants were Johnathan Hailey (35th, 21:13.28), Hunter Hines (40th, 21:36.34); Jason Shambles (43rd, 21:50.75); Drew Miller (48th, 22:17.12); Trevor Williams (51st, 22:34.21) and Alan Godfrey (53rd, 22:57.12). 
The Dewey girls squad — which head coach Lance Knight was bolstered by the late addition of some athletes — clawed to seventh place — just two spots shy of qualifying for state. The girls ran a two-mile distance. 
The Dewey girls varsity team included Knight (28th, 14:52.31); Janie Adams (43rd, 15:37.62); Makenna Carver (46th, 15:40.15); Kelsie Davis (50th, 16:02.56); Hailey Hamrick (51st, 16:03.46); and Morgan Richardson (60th, 16:38.03). Rules for posting comments
